modules.description: This module defines bitmask flags for initializing image loading formats in SDL2_image, supporting operations to combine and compare flag values. It works with the abstract type `t` representing format flags, using bitwise operations to test or check equality of flags. Concrete use cases include enabling specific image formats like PNG or JPEG when loading images with SDL2_image.

This module loads and saves images in various formats using SDL2_image, providing direct access to image file operations through functions like `load`, `save_png`, and format-specific variants. It works with `Sdl.surface` and `Sdl.texture` types, supporting concrete use cases such as loading PNG or JPEG files into textures for rendering, or saving surface data to PNG files. Additional functionality includes checking image format compatibility and reading XPM images from string arrays.

This module handles image file operations with functions to load and save images in formats like PNG, JPEG, and XPM, directly supporting `Sdl.surface` and `Sdl.texture` types. It enables concrete tasks such as loading an image file into a texture for rendering or exporting surface data to a PNG file. Additional capabilities include format compatibility checks and loading XPM images from string arrays.
